      <title>数学分析《每日一题》--2021.10.31</title>
      <link href="/2021/10/31/shu-xue-fen-xi-mei-ri-yi-ti-2021-10-31/"/>
      <url>/2021/10/31/shu-xue-fen-xi-mei-ri-yi-ti-2021-10-31/</url>
      
        <content type="html"><![CDATA[<p>题目如下：</p><script type="math/tex; mode=display">\label{con:inventoryflow}\tag{1}\large\lim_{n\rightarrow\infty}\frac{\tan(2\pi n!e)}{\ln(1+\frac{1}{n})}</script><p>这是一道非常常见的题，这里简单写一下。</p><p>首先对$\,e\,$进行$\,Taylor\,$展开：</p><script type="math/tex; mode=display">\tag{1.1}e=e^x|_{x=1}=\sum_{k=0}^{n}[\frac{1}{n}+\frac{1}{n+1}+\frac{e^{\theta_n}}{(n+2)!}]\;(0<{\theta_n}<1).</script><p>代入原式，得：</p><script type="math/tex; mode=display">\begin{aligned}原式&=\lim_{n\rightarrow\infty}n\tan\{2{\pi}n![\,\sum_{k=0}^{n}\frac{1}{k!}+\frac{1}{(n+1)!}+\frac{e^{\theta_n}}{(n+2)!}\,]\\\\&=\lim_{n\rightarrow\infty}n\tan{[\frac{2\pi}{(n+1)}}+\frac{2{\pi}e^{\theta_n}}{(n+1)(n+2)}]\\\\&=\lim_{n\rightarrow\infty}\frac{2{\pi}n}{(n+1)}+\frac{n}{(n+1)(n+2)}\,\cdot\,2\pi e^{\theta_n}\\\\&=2\pi\end{aligned}</script>]]></content>
      
      
