      <title>数学分析《每日一题》--2021.10.30</title>
      <link href="/2021/10/30/2021-10-30/"/>
      <url>/2021/10/30/2021-10-30/</url>
      
        <content type="html"><![CDATA[<p>题目如下：</p><script type="math/tex; mode=display">\label{con:inventoryflow}\tag{1}\large\lim_{n\rightarrow\infty}\frac{1}{\sqrt[n]{n!}}\sum_{k=1}^{n}\int_{1}^{\frac{k}{n}}e^{-{y}^{2}}dy</script><p>首先，有极限：</p><script type="math/tex; mode=display">\begin{equation}\tag{1.1}\lim_{n\rightarrow\infty}\frac{\sqrt[n]{n!}}{n}=\frac{1}{e}\end{equation}</script><p>所以对待求极限​，我们有：</p><script type="math/tex; mode=display">\begin{aligned}\lim_{n\rightarrow\infty}\frac{1}{\sqrt[n]{n!}}\sum_{k=1}^{n}\int_{1}^{\frac{k}{n}}e^{-{y}^{2}}dy&=\lim_{n\rightarrow\infty}\frac{e}{n} \sum_{k=1}^{n} \int_{1}^{\frac{k}{n}} e^{-{y}^{2}}dy\\\\&=e\int_{0}^{1}\bigg(\int_{1}^{x}e^{-{y}^{2}}dy \bigg)dx\\\\&=-e\int_{0}^{1} \bigg(\int_{x}^{1}e^{-{y}^{2}}dy \bigg)dx\\\\&=-e \int_{0}^{1}dy \int_{0}^{y} e^{-{y}^{2}}dx\\\\&=-e \int_{0}^{1} ye^{-y^2}dy\\\\&=\frac{1-e}{2}\end{aligned}</script>]]></content>
      
      
